5:1 Therefore be imitators of God, as dearly loved children; 
5:2 and walk in love, just as Messiah also loved us and gave Himself up for us as an offering and sacrifice to God for a fragrant aroma. 
5:3 . 
5:4 Obscene, coarse, and stupid talk are also out of place, but instead let there be thanksgiving. 
5:5 Know for certain that no immoral, indecent, or greedy person—who is really an idol worshipper at heart—has any inheritance in the kingdom of Messiah and God. 
5:6 Let no one deceive you with empty words, for because of such things God’s judgment comes on the children of disobedience. 
5:7 Therefore do not be partners with them. 
5:8 For once you were darkness, but now in union with the Lord you are light. Walk as children of light 
5:9 (for the fruit of light is in all goodness and righteousness and truth), 
5:10 trying to learn what is pleasing to the Lord. 
5:11 Take no part in the fruitless deeds of darkness, but rather expose them— 
5:12 for it is disgraceful even to mention the things that are done by them in secret. 
5:13 Yet everything exposed by the light is being made visible, 
5:14 for everything made visible is light. This is why it says, “Wake up, O sleeper! Rise from the dead, and Messiah will shine on you.” 
5:15 So pay close attention to how you walk—not as unwise people but as wise. 
5:16 Make the most of your time because the days are evil. 
5:17 For this reason do not be foolish, but understand what the Lord’s will is. 
